description.plain:
“Good Looking” is a portrait of lust, intimacy, and eventual loss as the singer attempts to navigate through the undiscovered lies of her past love experience, encapsulating these true moments which are now only memories. In a statement, Suki Waterhouse declared:

“Good Looking” is a representation of desire, attachment, and intimacy that captures the real moments in life, while uncovering the secrets buried within each of us. A girl and a boy embark on a journey that leads them to a burning love where nothing is what it seemed. Sometimes people are not destined to end up with each other. Nevertheless, the reflection always remains…

Released in October 2017, the slow-indie ballad gained attention in May 2022 when a sped-up version of the track went viral on TikTok.

In addition, the London-based artist traveled to New York City to create sultry visuals for the single. In a retro and timeless style, the music video follows Suki and her lover — played by Australian model Jordan Barrett — in the most intimate moments of life.

I’m not who I am to anyone, no, not me at all
 I’m not who I am to anyone these days, not at all
Here, Suki Is saying that she too isn’t herself around others or is misunderstood by the people around her like in the previous line.
You’re not who you are to anyone, to anyone
Here, Suki says that her “Good looking boy” isn’t himself around other or is misunderstood by the people around him.

I thought I’d uncovered your secrets but, turns out, there’s more
 You adored me before
She found out that he had cheated on her again and this broke her down. She just misses the time when he adored only her.
The skyline falls as I try to make sense of it all
She’s breaking down inside but still believes he’ll change.

Tides thrash inside, baby, I’m high octane
 Fever in a shock wave
 My core vibrates in an opium haze

She lives with insecurities inside and represents them as hazes and tides. These insecurities is because he cheated on her before but they are still together, maybe with false promises.

Saying it’s high octane implies that despite everything it hasn’t exploded yet, it pretends it’s fine to continue with he.

Play casino holes of my eyeballs

The reason why she asks him to use she as a replacement for casino places its because her asking him to see she as the place where he finds everything he is looking for and not anywhere else, she asks him not to cheat on her anymore.
Yet you think we’re the same
in the previous lyrics, she describes her intense emotions, and this line signifies that the target of the song believes they are in the same amount of pain

description.plain:
Three months after the release of the EP, Milk Teeth, Suki Waterhouse unveils the single, “To Love.” The track is unlike any of the British artist’s previous works — she exchanges her signature sad-girl heartbreak songwriting for a warmer and more optimistic take on romance.

“To Love” also showcases Waterhouse’s disbelief in her own happiness as she illustrates finding the right person at the right time. The singer, who has been dating British actor Robert Pattinson for four years, depicted a meditation on love and the joy it brings to life:

“To Love” is a song that I wrote really recently that I was going to wait to put out on my second album. But I felt like it is a very distinct portrait of my heart right now that I wanted to share.

Suki Waterhouse first performed the song on her ‘Coolest Place in the World’ tour, saying in a March 2023 interview with Rolling Stone:

I started performing it on tour and got so excited that I wanted to share it with everyone.

annotations:
Handing out gold stars for tailor-made behaviour
 I can see your demons shining like prizes
 I’m sat out on the balcony
 Too sad to go to the party
 It’s a crime loving you so, it’s a crime letting you go

Appearance/Reality: She is frustrated that nobody sees through her partners act of their ‘tailor-made behaviour’ but also hints that she is caught up in it as well. She still loves them and presents it as something taboo or frustrating as she knows it’s just an act, however continues to do so

Deep horrible blues
 Watching you work the room

Perhaps suggesting her partner isn’t as authentic as they seem and by working the room she’s implying they put on a persona around other people in order to be well liked. This could have caused her ‘deep horrible blues’ as she feels isolated in her knowledge of them and feels betrayed and frustrated that no one else sees through the facade.
Could also allude to the idea that they’re  more interested in being likeable and well known than paying attention to their partner

annotations:
Love is held in the cathedral
 God exists between people, homie

These lyrics might be an allusion to the iconic 1995 movie Before Sunrise, where a young American man, Jesse, and French student, Celine, spontaneously get off a train together and fall in love over one night in Vienna before they must part ways. At one point, Celine says:

I believe if there’s any kind of God it wouldn’t be in any of us, not you or me but just this little space in between. If there’s any kind of magic in this world it must be in the attempt of understanding someone sharing something. I know, it’s almost impossible to succeed but who cares really? The answer must be in the attempt.

The film also has a scene where Jesse and Celine visit a cathedral and discuss love, family, and life.
